ive exploration of his groundbreaking achievements in cinema, the book considers Schrader’s more overlooked films and provides new insights to their connection with his celebrated work in direction and screenwriting such as Taxi Driver (1976), Cat People (1982) and The Comfort of Strangers (1990).  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mai 2023) 4aFilm, Media & Cultural Studies. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh1 aAllison, Deborah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBachman, Erik M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBalcerzak, Scott, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrems, Brian, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aBrems, Brian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDassanowsky, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoore, Michelle E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoulton, Erica, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPrasch, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aProrokova, Tatiana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRibera, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSlaymaker, James, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStevenson, Billy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z97831107804130 cprintz978147446203740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781474462051423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781474462051/original  a978-3-11-078041-3  Edinburgh University